detail.content: achtung berlin: Tisch School of the Arts at NYU                           Skip to content        ITP - Interactive Telecommunications About the Program Inside ITP Remembering Red Burns  home > ITP        Achtung Berlin - New Berlin Film Award / Programme Towards Berlin  Congratulations to ITP students Maria Mayer and Tom Ainslie! Their documentary video, "Berlin / Detroit" has been selected to be screened during the New Berlin Film Awards.    About "Berlin / Detroit":    This piece is an experimental documentary about the urban environments of Berlin and Detroit. Each of the cities has undergone dramatic changes over the course of the last 100 years, and in each case that history has been repressed to some degree. Detroit was left abandoned as residents fled the city for suburban comfort, while Berlin rebuilt itself following the fall of the Wall.       ---    Towards Berlin is organized within the framework achtung berlin - new berlin film award which will take place from 14. -17. April 2005 in the Hackesche Höfe Filmtheater in Berlin, Germany.    How is Berlin viewed by national and international filmmakers?    Towards Berlin shows how filmmakers from around the world engage themselves thematically with Berlin, how they establish their perspectives on the city, and how they form an aesthetic picture.    Berlin is today, more than ever, a starting-point for filmmakers from Germany, Western- and Eastern Europe, as well from as overseas, who seek - with a camera in their hand - the new 'Berlin Myth', accompanied by very personal depictions of a life in this city.    An independent jury, composed of figures from the film and television industries, is responsible for allocating the "new berlin film award" in the category Best Berlin film as well as several other prizes and accolades.    achtung berlin - new berlin film award is a project of achtung berlin e.V., in cooperation with the Hackesche Höfe Filmtheater and film.lounge.berlin.    The Shortfilm Programme of Berlin Highlights is presented by interfilm berlin.    achtung berlin - new berlin film award is supported by the Hauptstadtkulturfonds.    http://www.achtungberlin.de     ITP Admissions, Special Events and Alumni Coordinator Midori Yasuda 721 Broadway, 4th Floor New York, NY 10003               Phone:       212 998 1882 midori.yasuda@nyu.edu           Undergraduate Admissions Graduate Admissions Academic Services Student Life Financial Aid and Scholarships Career Development Counseling Services International Students Incoming Students Graduation Forms What is Special Programs? achtung berlin: Tisch School of the Arts at NYU                           Skip to content        ITP - Interactive Telecommunications About the Program Inside ITP Remembering Red Burns  home > ITP        Achtung Berlin - New Berlin Film Award / Programme Towards Berlin  Congratulations to ITP students Maria Mayer and Tom Ainslie! Their documentary video, "Berlin / Detroit" has been selected to be screened during the New Berlin Film Awards.    About "Berlin / Detroit":    This piece is an experimental documentary about the urban environments of Berlin and Detroit. Each of the cities has undergone dramatic changes over the course of the last 100 years, and in each case that history has been repressed to some degree. Detroit was left abandoned as residents fled the city for suburban comfort, while Berlin rebuilt itself following the fall of the Wall.       ---    Towards Berlin is organized within the framework achtung berlin - new berlin film award which will take place from 14. -17. April 2005 in the Hackesche Höfe Filmtheater in Berlin, Germany.    How is Berlin viewed by national and international filmmakers?    Towards Berlin shows how filmmakers from around the world engage themselves thematically with Berlin, how they establish their perspectives on the city, and how they form an aesthetic picture.    Berlin is today, more than ever, a starting-point for filmmakers from Germany, Western- and Eastern Europe, as well from as overseas, who seek - with a camera in their hand - the new 'Berlin Myth', accompanied by very personal depictions of a life in this city.    An independent jury, composed of figures from the film and television industries, is responsible for allocating the "new berlin film award" in the category Best Berlin film as well as several other prizes and accolades.    achtung berlin - new berlin film award is a project of achtung berlin e.V., in cooperation with the Hackesche Höfe Filmtheater and film.lounge.berlin.    The Shortfilm Programme of Berlin Highlights is presented by interfilm berlin.    achtung berlin - new berlin film award is supported by the Hauptstadtkulturfonds.    http://www.achtungberlin.de     ITP Admissions, Special Events and Alumni Coordinator Midori Yasuda 721 Broadway, 4th Floor New York, NY 10003               Phone:       212 998 1882 midori.yasuda@nyu.edu           Undergraduate Admissions Graduate Admissions Academic Services Student Life Financial Aid and Scholarships Career Development Counseling Services International Students Incoming Students Graduation Forms What is Special Programs?
